# Google Cloud Project Configuration
# Your Google Cloud Project ID
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=your-project-id

# Optional: Google Slides Template ID
# The Slide ID after the /d/ in the URL for default export template
SLIDE_TEMPLATE=your-slide-template-id

# Optional: BigQuery Data Source
# BigQuery datasource name
bq_DATASOURCE=your-bigquery-datasource

# ============================================
# IMPORTANT: Secrets Configuration
# ============================================
# The following secrets should be configured in Google Cloud Secret Manager
# instead of environment variables for security reasons:
#
# Required Secrets in Secret Manager:
# ------------------------------------
# 1. client_secret
#    - Your OAuth Client ID credentials JSON file
#    - Create at: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#    - Upload the entire client_secret.json content
#
# 2. flask_secret_key
#    - A random security key for Flask sessions
#    - Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
#    - More info: https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.3.x/config/#SECRET_KEY
#
# 3. developer_token
#    - Your Google Ads developer token
#    - Find at: https://ads.google.com/aw/apicenter
#
# 4. image_bucket
#    - Google Cloud Storage bucket name for images (publicly viewable)
#    - Must grant allUsers as "Storage Object Viewer"
#    - Must grant service account as "Storage Object User"
#
# How to add secrets to Secret Manager:
# 1. Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/security/secret-manager
# 2. Create each secret with the exact names listed above
# 3. Upload the values as described
#
# For local development:
# ----------------------
# You may create a .env file (which is gitignored) with these values
# for local testing, but production should ALWAYS use Secret Manager.
